, but you must include with your application both: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the child&rsquo;s full birth certificate showing both parents&rsquo; details</li>\n  <li>evidence of the British parent&rsquo;s nationality status (eg passport details or <a href=\"/apply-first-adult-passport/documents-you-must-send-with-your-application\" title=\"documents to prove British nationality\">other original documents you can send</a> if they don&rsquo;t have a British passport)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You should also send any of the following that apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the parental order (if one is held) </li>\n  <li>proof of marriage or civil partnership (if this is relevant to the claim) </li>\n  <li>evidence of treatment, eg a letter from the clinic where it took place</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You might be asked to provide more documents depending on your circumstances. </p>\n\n<p>If you need help or your circumstances are more complicated, contact the Passport Adviceline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Passport Adviceline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://contact.homeoffice.gov.uk/contact.php?survey=1&amp;pager=2\" title=\"enquiry form\" rel=\"external\">Enquiry form</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0300 222 0000<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0300 222 0222  <br />\n<strong>Text Relay:</strong> 18001 0300 222 0000<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm  <br />\nSaturday, Sunday and public holidays, 9am to 5:30pm</p>\n</div>\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-11-14T11:38:43+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Passports","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship%2Fpassports.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Eligibility, fees, applying, renewing and updating","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=citizenship%2Fpassports","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/citizenship/passports"},"parent":{"title":"Citizenship and life in the UK","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship.json","web_url":null,"deta