ntity and Passport Service (<abbr title=\"Identity and Passport Service\">IPS</abbr>) may need to contact you for more information.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>When you need to renew your passport</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a new passport if you&rsquo;ve changed your:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>name (by marriage, civil partnership or deed poll)</li>\n  <li>appearance and you can&rsquo;t be recognised in your current passport photo (eg because of major facial surgery or trauma, piercings or tattoos)</li>\n  <li>gender (even if your name remains the same)</li>\n  <li>nationality status (eg from a British subject to a British citizen)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You follow the same application process for <a href=\"/renew-adult-passport\" title=\"Renew your adult passport\">renewing your passport</a>, but you&rsquo;ll need to include specific documents with your application form - check below for what you need.</p>\n\n<p>You get up to 9 months extra time on a new passport to cover time left on your old one.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Sign your application form using your new name.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>When you don&rsquo;t need to renew your passport</h2>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need a new passport if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>change your job, title, address or contact details</li>\n  <li>emigrate</li>\n  <li>change your marital status but keep your name</li>\n  <li>get nationality of another country as well as your British nationality</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re getting married or forming a civil partnership</h2>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Decide whether to change your name before or after the ceremony - the name on your passport must be the same one you use when you book your travel.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Before the ceremony</h3>\n\n<p>You can change the name on your passport up to 3 months before the ceremony. Your old passport will be cancelled. </p>\n\n<p>The new passport is &lsquo;postdated&rsquo; - you can&rsquo;t use it before the ceremony. </p>\n\n<p>Some countries won&rsquo;t issue visas for post-dated passports - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-us/what-we-do/protocol/embassies-in-uk/\" title=\"foreign embassies in the UK\">check with the country&rsquo;s consulate.</a></p>\n\n<p>You must send a standard passport application form, along with the form &lsquo;Passports for newly weds and civil partners&rsquo;, signed by the religious minister or registrar who will conduct the ceremony.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@travel/documents/digitalasset/dg_175797.pdf\" title=\"Download the 'Passports for newly weds and civil partners' form (PDF, 112KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Passports for newly weds and civil partners form’ (PDF, 112KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@travel/documents/digitalasset/dg_175796.pdf\" title=\"Download the 'Passports for newly weds and civil partners' leaflet (PDF, 144KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Passports for newly weds and civil partners leaflet’ (PDF, 144KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>After the ceremony</h3>\n\n<p>Send the standard passport application along with your marriage or civil partnership certificate. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Any unexpired visas in your old passport may become invalid - check with the country’s consulate.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Going back to your unmarried (maiden) name</h2>\n\n<p>You must send with your application form:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your birth certificate</li>\n  <li>a signed statement saying you&rsquo;ve gone back to your maiden name for all purposes</li>\n  <li>a decree absolute showing both names if you&rsquo;ve divorced</li>\n  <li>a marriage certificate showing both names</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>If you can&rsquo;t be recognised in your current passport photo</h2>\n\n<p>Make sure that your application form and 1 of your <a href=\"/photos-for-passports\" title=\"Passport photo requirements\">passport photos</a> is countersigned by an appropriate person. </p>\n\n<h2>Titles you can use on your passport</h2>\n\n<p>You can ask to include titles on your passport like:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>professional titles - eg doctor, judge, minister of religion, professor or QC </li>\n  <li>honours or military decorations</li>\n  <li>JP if you&rsquo;re a magistrate</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Put the details in section 2 of the application form and enclose evidence of your title.</p>\n\n<h2>Change of gender</h2>\n\n<p>Send one of the following with your application and supporting documents:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a letter from a doctor or chartered psychologist who practices in gender dysphoria stating that you have a need to live in a different gender, and evidence of your change of name (eg your deed poll)</li>\n  <li>a <a href=\"/apply-gender-recognition-certificate\" title=\"Applying for a Gender Recognition Certificate\">gender recognition certificate</a></li>\n  <li>a new birth or adoption certificate showing your acquired gender</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can download more advice about passports for transsexual and transgender people.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@government/documents/digitalasset/dg_202401.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Applying for a passport - additional information for transgender and transsexual customers' (PDF, 235KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Applying for a passport - additional information for transgender and transsexual customers’ (PDF, 235KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Changing your name by deed poll</h2>\n\n<p>Send your change of name deed with your application form.  </p>\n\n<h2>Name changes that don&rsquo;t match birth, naturalisation or registration certificates</h2>\n\n<p>You must send extra evidence with your application. The <abbr title=\"Identity and Passport Service\">IPS</abbr> will need to see documents showing both the date of and reason for your name change. </p>\n\n<p>You must send original documents, not copies. Laminated documents can be used as proof for name changes. </p>\n\n<h2>Get help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>Call the Passport Adviceline if you need help.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Passport Adviceline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0300 222 0000<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0300 222 0222  <br />\n<strong>Text Relay:</strong> 18001 0300 222 0000<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm  <br />\nSaturday, Sunday and public holidays, 9am to 5:30pm</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:25:27+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Passports","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship%2Fpassports.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Eligibility, fees, applying, renewing and updating","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=citizenship%2Fpassports","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/citizenship/passports"},"parent":{"title":"Citizenship and life in the UK","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes voting and how government works","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=citizenship","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/citizenship"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Passports and travelling abroad","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/driving%2Fpassports-travelling-abroad.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes driving abroad, getting a passport, pet passports and bringing goods into the UK","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=driving%2Fpassports-travelling-abroad","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/driving/passports-travelling-abroad"},"parent":{"title":"Driving, transport an